extendedInfo.description: ATMs offer extraordinary convenience, providing anytime access to cash and account information in the smallest towns and the biggest cities. However, if you use an ATM not affiliated with your own financial institution, you might be required to pay an additional fee for the convenience.The SUM Program allows you to save time and money by offering surcharge-free access to a wide array of ATMs. If your financial institution is a SUM Program member, you can use any SUM-designated ATM without paying a surcharge.Finding SUM ATMs has never been easier when using our ATM locator App. From the convenience of your phone, you can find the location of the closest SUM ATM by entering an address, Zip Code or your exact location using the GPS on your phone.The SUM ATM locator is easy to use and offers these benefits:â¢	Search for SUM surcharge free ATMs using your current location, or enter an address or simply a Zip Codeâ¢	Provides addresses and distance information to closest ATMsâ¢	Provides convenient turn-by-turn directions to the ATMâ¢	Provides a link to Google Mapsâ¢	Itâs free

reviews.title: Fail.
reviews.comment: Problems: (1) Ignores the GPS location. (2) Does not show names of participating ATMs, but only addresses. (3) The directions feature always assumes that the trip is starting from home.
reviews.author: Richard Chonak

reviews.title: Sucks
reviews.comment: This app is just that. It sucks. I went to 5 banks all were suppose to be SUM and they where not. Fix and upgrade so people can provide feed back.
reviews.author: Joshua K

reviews.title: Works well
reviews.comment: Simple, yet effective app!  Does exactly what you would expect - would like the option to map all search results at once.
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.comment: What crap! Worked the first time I opened it, now the only thing it says is that there are no ATMs within 20 miles. Don\'t bother.
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: Not there when you need it
reviews.comment: Doesn\'t work or crashes when you need it the most, often get a \"server not responding\" error mesaage. Tells me to drive for miles even if less than a block away from a SUM machine.
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: marginal
reviews.comment: Surprisingly, this is worse than the terrible web site.  It worked once, but doesn\'t return bank names, only addresses.  After one use, it stopped working until a re-boot.  2 stars because when it works, it might get you to an atm.
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: Works sometimes
reviews.comment: Doesn\'t work. \"No ATMs within 20 miles \" in front of a SUM ATM. T-Mobile G2
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: Doesn\'t find closest ATM
reviews.comment: The closest ATM is .4mi away but it is in another town. When I ask for the closest to my location, I get one 1.1mi away in my town.
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: Poorly implemented
reviews.comment: Doesn\'t find nearest atm. This is as bad as the website.

reviews.title: tells me something about Geocode
reviews.comment: This app sucks, I keep getting some type of Geocode error. yes I did need this app and it will not work for me. I don\'t even want to rate it one star

reviews.title: Not good.
reviews.comment: Pretty bad app.  Didn\'t find an ATM based on my current location, found one based on an hours old location. Everything else knew where I was.
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: Sometimey
reviews.comment: The app can\'t find an ATM within 20 miles of my zip code even though my credit union is 6 miles away.  Website has same problem.

reviews.title: Not a well written app.
reviews.comment: Worked the first time when I used Google location services on my Android. The second time it came back with no locations found writing 20 miles and gave me an error that the GPS isn\'t on. I tried to use the zip code feature but that returned nothing also when I know there are 5 locations writhing 2 miles of my zip.
reviews.author: Jason M

reviews.title: HORRIBLE
reviews.comment: Tried use current location... gave me results in a different state. Used zip code.. gives only street addresses.... I guess we are supposed to know what city they are in. Such a simple concept. Hoe could they screw it up so bad?
